EmailTemplate.subject: Invitation: IB Open Evening 13 June, 2017
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Lead.FirstName}
IB Open Evening Discover a world of opportunities
I am delighted to invite you and your family to our upcoming IB Open Evening.
The IB Diploma offers students a broad range of learning skills and subject areas, providing a truly international curriculum that is taught in 150 countries worldwide.
Hear from students and staff about managing study schedules, subject choices, post-school options and what it means to be part of a global community of learners.
Any interested students and their parents are welcome to join us.
5.30pm, Tuesday 13 June
M C Newth Auditorium
Bishop Barry Centre
St Andrew's Cathedral School Senior College Campus
51 Druitt Street
Sydney
The evening commences with a welcome from our Head of School, Dr Collier followed by presentations from our Director of Learning, Mrs Sharon Munro and past and current IB students. There will also be guest speakers on the evening.
Bookings essential: RSVP https://www.sacs.nsw.edu.au/tourselect/1096
I look forward to welcoming you to this exciting event.
Kind regards
Bruce Perry Registrar/Mathematics Teacher
You are receiving this invitation as you have previously indicated interest in Senior College enrolment at St Andrew’s Cathedral School. We would love you to visit our city school however, if you would like to unsubscribe from further invitations, please click here.
